### Real-time Monitoring
```bash
# Follow all container logs
docker-compose logs -f

# Follow specific service logs
docker logs -f traefik
docker logs -f authelia
docker logs -f plex
```

### Health Status Dashboard
```bash
# Create a simple status check script
cat > /opt/homelabarr-cli/status_check.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash
echo "=== HomelabARR CLI Status ==="
echo "Date: $(date)"
echo ""

services=("traefik" "authelia" "plex" "sonarr")
for service in "${services[@]}"; do
    if docker ps | grep -q "$service"; then
        health=$(docker inspect "$service" 2>/dev/null | jq -r '.[0].State.Health.Status // "no-health-check"')
        echo "✅ $service: Running ($health)"
    else
        echo "❌ $service: Not running"
    fi
done

echo ""
echo "=== Resource Usage ==="
docker stats --no-stream --format "table {{.Name}}\\t{{.CPUPerc}}\\t{{.MemUsage}}\\t{{.MemPerc}}"
EOF

chmod +x /opt/homelabarr-cli/status_check.sh
```

## 🚨 **Troubleshooting**

### Common Issues
```bash
# Permission issues
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/appdata
sudo chmod -R 755 /opt/appdata

# Network issues
docker network prune
docker network create proxy

# Service startup issues
docker-compose down
docker system prune -f
docker-compose up -d
```

### Reset Everything
```bash
# Nuclear option - reset everything
docker-compose down
docker system prune -af
docker volume prune -f
sudo rm -rf /opt/appdata/*
# Then re-run deployment steps
```

